This paper deals with the problem of efficient data gathering in a wireless network, which is a common topic in the field of computer networks and communication systems (cs.NI). The focus on minimizing the maximum flow time of a data packet suggests that the paper may involve algorithms and optimization techniques (cs.DS, cs.AL). The use of resource augmentation is a common technique in the design and analysis of algorithms (cs.DC), and the paper may also involve information theory (cs.IT) as it deals with the transmission of data packets in a wireless network.
